b'A detailed look at the program'
b'Interdisciplinary Experience'
b'Our program is truly an interdisciplinary experience, with\xc2\xa0faculty, researchers, and students coming from backgrounds in health, education, assistive technology, social sciences\xc2\xa0and humanities.\xc2\xa0We recognize the inherent tensions that exist between therapeutic, medical and social models of disability, but acknowledge these differences as fertile ground for the development of disability studies as an\xc2\xa0integrative knowledge base.'
b'Your career'
b'Students enroll in our program for a variety of reasons and with a variety of goals for when they graduate, including\xc2\xa0academic positions, disability policy and advocacy, and visual or performing arts.'
b'A PhD in\xc2\xa0disability\xc2\xa0studies gives you\xc2\xa0advanced knowledge about complex social implications of disability. You\xe2\x80\x99ll develop the\xc2\xa0skills to lead research, policy analysis, and program evaluation and\xc2\xa0development in ways that best address the perspectives of people with disabilities.'
b"Ryan Parrey-Munger '13 "
b'Ryan is exploring interactions between people with and without disabilities'
b'\n                Meet Ryan\n            '
b'Joe Caldwell \xe2\x80\x9905'
b'Joe is applying research to make a difference in people\xe2\x80\x99s lives'
