b"Luca Badetti '15 "
b'Luca sees similarities among differences'
b'\n                Meet Luca\n            '
b'Learn from the best'
b'Sarah Parker Harris'
b'Focusing on comparative and national disability policy and legislation, employment, entrepreneurship and social entrepreneurship'
b'\n                Meet Sarah\n            '
b'Kruti Acharya'
b'Research themes include the role of childhood, family and community adversity in the health disparities experienced by individuals with disabilities and the ethics of genetic testing for disability in various contexts '
b'\n                Meet Kruti\n            '
b'Sandy Sufian '
b'Research focusing on the history of disability, childhood and family and the intersections\nbetween disability, medicine, and public health'
b'\n                Meet Sandy\n            '
b'\n                Meet our faculty\n            '
b'DHD Connections'
b'Our program provides you with the opportunity to embrace interdisciplinary education beyond the classroom and link to the disability community.\xc2\xa0 By joining DHD you will become a part of our collaborative network of diverse faculty, staff, students, and partners including people with disabilities, family members, organizations, academic departments and universities in Illinois, nationally and internationally.\xc2\xa0 Build your experience through DHD connections:'
b'Some of our past students have worked in policy positions at legal and government centers in Washington, D.C., learning about policy-making processes that affect the lives of disabled citizens and their families. Others have traveled internationally to conduct research, present papers, and participate in service initiatives as they learn how the disability studies knowledge base can expand to incorporate experiences of disability in many cultures.'
b'Drew Egli visits the Wolfensberger Archives '
b'DHD PhD student Drew Egli\xc2\xa0was provided with the\xc2\xa0opportunity to\xc2\xa0visit the Wolfensberger Archives in Omaha as part of a collaboration with the Nebraska UCEDD (the Munroe-Meyer Institute) and the UNMC library.'
b"\n                    Learn more about Drew's experience \n                "
